	  <concept id="i1103371"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">17.109</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d1048e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1062e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1057120.dita#i1057120"
                        base="i1057120"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.217-2</xref>, Cancellation Under Multi-year Contracts, in solicitations and contracts when a multi-year contract is contemplated.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1062e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Economic price adjustment clauses</i>. Economic price adjustment clauses are adaptable to multi-year contracting needs. When the period of production is likely to warrant a labor and material costs contingency in the contract price, the contracting officer should normally use an economic price adjustment clause (see <xref href="FAR-i1104876.dita#i1104876"
                        base="i1104876"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.203</xref>). When contracting for services, the contracting officer-</p>
					          <ol id="d1048e41" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1062e45" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Shall add the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1056443.dita#i1056443"
                              base="i1056443"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-43</xref>, Fair Labor Standards Act and Service Contract Labor Standards- Price Adjustment (Multiple Year and Option Contracts), when the contract includes the clause at <xref href="FAR-i52_222_41.dita#i52_222_41"
                              base="i1056332"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-41</xref>, Service Contract Labor Standards;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1062e60" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                May modify the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1056443.dita#i1056443"
                              base="i1056443"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-43</xref> in overseas contracts when laws, regulations, or international agreements require contractors to pay higher wage rates; or</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1062e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                May use an economic price adjustment clause authorized by <xref href="FAR-i1104876.dita#i1104876"
                              base="i1104876"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.203</xref>, when potential fluctuations require coverage and are not included in cost contingencies provided for by the clause at <xref href="FAR-i1056443.dita#i1056443"
                              base="i1056443"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.222-43</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
